The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, December 28, 2002 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE CD				 																																	(Satinath Mukhopadhyay)				 																																	lElocutionist Satinath Mukhopadhyay has ganged up with a dozen kids in this fun-filled album of songs, stories and nursery rhymes. Two of Sanjib Chattopadhyays stories, Abatar and Mahaprasthan, have been stitched with Lankakando, a set of 39 limericks scripted by Apurba Datta.				 																THE FILM				 																																	(Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, December 28, 6 pm)				 																																	lThe Woody Allen film revolves around a New York writers creative and erotic life. With a star cast including Billy Crystal, Demi Moore, Kirstie Alley and Allen himself, the film is shot in some of Manhattans best known landmarks.				 																THE EVENTS				 																																	(Tollygunge Club and Space Circle, Dec 31, 8.30 pm)				 																																	lPalash Sens Euphoria and DJ Austin at Tolly Club and Bombay Vikings with DJ Akash at Space Circle will kick off the nights festivities, in association with The Telegraph. 				 																THE BOOK				 																																	(Neepabithi Ghosh)				 																																	lA balanced insight into the making of the legend and the life of the man behind the actors mask. Contains rare photographs and an informative filmography and bibliography.
